BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Is Inflammation?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Inflammation is your body's natural defense mechanism. When you get a cut or infection,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (acute inflammation helps you heal. However, when inflammation becomes chronic - lasting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (weeks, months, or years - it can damage healthy tissue and contribute to serious health) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (conditions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 586.4 Td (Acute vs. Chronic Inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (Acute inflammation: Short-term response to injury or infection. Signs include redness,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (swelling, heat, and pain. This is healthy and necessary.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (Chronic inflammation: Low-grade, persistent inflammation that can last months or years.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (Often has no obvious symptoms initially but damages tissues over time.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 500.6 Td (Common Signs of Chronic Inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 484.6 Td (- Persistent fatigue and low energy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 470.6 Td (- Joint pain or stiffness) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 456.6 Td (- Digestive problems \(bloating, gas, irregular bowels\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 442.6 Td (- Skin issues \(eczema, psoriasis, acne\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 428.6 Td (- Brain fog and difficulty concentrating) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 414.6 Td (- Frequent infections or slow healing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 400.6 Td (- Weight gain, especially around the midsection) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 386.6 Td (- Mood changes, anxiety, or depression) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 356.8 Td (What Causes Chronic Inflammation?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 338.8 Td (- Poor diet high in processed foods, sugar, and refined carbs) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 324.8 Td (- Sedentary lifestyle and lack of movement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 310.8 Td (- Chronic stress and poor sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 296.8 Td (- Environmental toxins and pollutants) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 282.8 Td (- Gut dysbiosis and food sensitivities) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 268.8 Td (- Excess body fat, particularly visceral fat) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 254.8 Td (- Smoking and excessive alcohol consumption) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 225.0 Td (The Role of Diet in Inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 207.0 Td (Research consistently shows that dietary patterns play a major role in either promoting or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 193.0 Td (reducing inflammation. The Standard American Diet \(SAD\) is highly inflammatory due to its) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 179.0 Td (reliance on processed foods, added sugars, refined oils, and artificial additives.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 151.2 Td (Inflammatory Foods to Reduce) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 135.2 Td (- Refined sugars and high-fructose corn syrup) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 121.2 Td (- Trans fats and partially hydrogenated oils) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 107.2 Td (- Refined carbohydrates \(white bread, pastries\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 93.2 Td (- Processed meats \(hot dogs, sausages, deli meats\)) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
